702118f-a.title: Bronx: Westchester Avenue - Castle Hill Avenue
702118f-a.text:
Westchester Avenue, north side, east from a point midway
between Castle Hill and Glebe Avenues. Westchester Avenue,
upon which is the elevated structure of the I.R.T. subway,
bends northward alightly beyond Glebe Avenue.
April 16, 1938
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS

702119f-a.title: Bronx: Westchester Avenue - Castle Hill
702119f-a.text:
Vestchester Avenue, south side, between Castle Hill and
Glebe Avenues, showing an old 2-story frame house, located on
the grounds of bt. Peters Rectory. The view is from underneath
the elevated trestle of the I.R.T. subway.
April 16, 1938
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
